<item>
            <title>[SOLR-4201] Combination of a core being swappable and loading on startup doesn&apos;t actually load on startup</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4201</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;See Shawn&apos;s comment on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1028&quot; title=&quot;Automatic core loading unloading for multicore&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-1028&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-1028&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Problem is this line (611 currently) in CoreContainer.xml (4x)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; if (!p.isSwappable() &amp;amp;&amp;amp; p.isLoadOnStartup())&lt;br/&gt;
Should be || instead I think.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
